The study, which was published in the Journal of Family Psychology, surveyed 1,000 women who had divorced in the past five years.

The women were asked to rate their experience of divorce on a scale of one to 10, with one being the most positive and 10 being the worst.

The results showed that 60 per-cent of women were happy with their divorce, while 40 per-cent said they were not.

The study also found that women who were divorced were more likely to be happy with their marriages than women who had not.

The researchers said the results showed the importance of having a positive attitude towards divorce.

“Divorce is a very important part of the life of a woman, and it is important to have a positive attitude towards it,” said Dr. Susanne Schmid, a psychologist at the University.

“It is important that women are able to talk about their experiences and to be able to share their experiences with others.”

The study also found women who had been married for more than 10 years were more satisfied with their relationships than women with less than 10 years of marriage.

The researchers said this was because women who married for longer were more confident in their relationships.

The study also found women who divorced were more content with their lives than women not divorced.
